<DOC><DOCNO> AP890620-0040 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-20-89 0439EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Korea-Shooting     06-20 0201</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Korea-Shooting,0205</SECOND><HEAD>Korean Fisherman Apparently Shot by U.S. Helicopter</HEAD><DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A South Korean fisherman was apparentlyhit by gunfire from a U.S. Marine helicopter taking part in gunnerypractice, the U.S. military said in a statement today.   The fisherman, Sohn Dal-gun, was hit by a bullet Monday whilefishing with two other men in the Yellow Sea off the west coast, thestatement said. The bullet apparently came from a Marine helicopterpracticing at the Koon-ni military target range on the nearby shore,it said.   A U.S. officer, who declined to be named, said the fisherman washit in the hand and the foot, but was not seriously hurt. The twoother fishermen in the boat were not hurt.   The incident was under investigation, the statement said.   Koon-ni Range, which is under U.S. military control, has been atthe center of a dispute with local farmers demanding the facility beclosed and the land turned over to them. Ten U.S. Air Forcepersonnel were hurt last month when about 150 South Koreans stormedthe range to demand it be closed.   The United States has some 43,000 troops based in South Koreaunder a joint defense treaty.</TEXT></DOC>